fered to have them removed from the official record of debate. Sen. <PERSON> Ernest </PERSON> <PERSON> Hollings </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-S.C. </LOCATION>, had used such language already this week. The exchange set off the round of Republican complaints about leaks, and led <PERSON> Nunn </PERSON> to say the <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> had been guilty of the same thing in reverse _ claiming that the report contained nothing to disqualify Tower without disclosing the allegations.
