's biracial business climate would survive the ruling `` The program allowed us to develop certain relationships,'' said <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Cordy </PERSON>, president of <ORGANIZATION> AMC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mechanical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Contractors </ORGANIZATION>, one of the partners in the construction of the Underground <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> entertainment complex. `` Those relationships will go on. People will continue to do business as we have.'' <LOCATION> Fulton </LOCATION> and DeKalb counties, which include parts of <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION>, have goals of 20 percent minority participation in county contracts. Their programs were not affected by the ruling Thursday, but the <LOCATION> Fulton </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> program is being challenged in federal court.
