<HEAD>Rebels Call Boycott of March 19 Presidential Vote</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DOUGLAS GRANT MINE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Leftist rebels on Friday called for a boycott of the presidential election scheduled for March 19, saying the vote would aggravate war and poverty. The insurgents have proposed postponement of the election until September. They said if the vote were put off, they would participate and respect its outcome. `` We call on the our people not to vote March 19,'' said the <ORGANIZATION> Farabundo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marti </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION> on its clandestine radio station. Despite more than five weeks of debate on the guerrilla proposal, the <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> government and the insurgents have not been able to agree on when, where or how to negotiate its possible implementation. A leftist electoral front on Friday accused the government and the rightist <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nationalist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alliance </ORGANIZATION>, or <PERSON> Arena </PERSON>, of procrastinating in response to the plan. Arena controls the legislature and is favored to win the presidential election. It is adamantly opposed to postponement of the vote. `` The <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Arena </PERSON> are trying to take advantage of the situation for propagandistic electoral ends, thus manipulating the people's desire for peace,'' said the leftist Democratic Convergence. It alleged in a communique that the two parties intend to prevent postponement by stalling until March 19. The leftist alliance proposed rescheduling the election July 9. It also said the government, the <ORGANIZATION> FMLN </ORGANIZATION> and representatives of the political parties should meet in <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> next week to negotiate an end to the 9-year-old civil war. `` The election of March 19 is designed to sustain the war after the previous five flawed elections have aggravated the original causes of the conflict,'' said the rebels on Radio Venceremos. `` We have proposed to compete in the political sphere, in which clear and clean results would conciliate the parties in conflict in light of the inviability of continuing the war,'' they said. `` But those who have made a living from the war have sought to close the doors to peace.'' `` The elections of March 19 will only aggravate hunger and misery, as they hold out no hope of real solution for the country's crisis,'' the rebels said
