 </PERSON>, who has both <LOCATION> Dutch </LOCATION> and Filipino citizenship, is a member of the central committee of the outlawed <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Jalandoni </PERSON> is believed to be in charge of rebel fund-raising activities in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>. Mrs. <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON> opened peace talks with the Front in 1986 but negotiations collapsed in January 1987 after she refused rebel power-sharing demands. Last week, Front spokesman <PERSON> Satur </PERSON> <PERSON> Ocampo </PERSON> said the rebels would consider resuming peace talks if the Aquino government agreed to close the six <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> military bases here when their lease expires in 1991. Also Thursday, police said <PERSON> Capistrano </PERSON> <PERSON> Legaspi </PERSON>, mayor of the town of <LOCATION> Kinogitan </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Misamis </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Oriental </LOCATION> province, was slain Wednesday by three suspected rebel assassins. The report said <LOCATION> Legaspi </LOCATION> was waiting for a ride home when the rebels approached and opened fire in the town about 470 miles southeast of <LOCATION> Manila </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Legaspi </PERSON> was an outspoken opponent of the rebel movement.
