 <PERSON> Terry </PERSON> <PERSON> Rakolta </PERSON> unexpectedly won a skirmish and now she wants to start a battle against what she says are sexually oriented and violent programs that cut into the network television fare her children can watch. The 40-year-old mother of four, offended by the off-color humor on the prime-time series `` Married ... With Children,'' conveyed her distaste to the show's major advertisers in a flurry of letters starting in January. Much to Mrs. <PERSON> Rakolta </PERSON>'s surprise, the letters prompted two of the nation's largest advertisers, <ORGANIZATION> Proctor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Gamble </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> McDonalds </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, and several others to pull their commercials from the series, the top-rated program on the fledgling <ORGANIZATION> Fox </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> network.
