<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The stock market showed some scattered gains today in an indecisive session. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 8.04 to 2,273.75 by 3 p.m. on Wall Street. Gainers outnumbered losers by about 4 to 3 in nationwide trading of <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> Exchange-listed issues, with 780 up, 587 down and 524 unchanged. The <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> reported that the index of leading economic indicators rose 0.6 percent in January, in line with advance estimates on the Street. The figures elicited no strong response from the bond market, where prices were mixed. In the absence of any stimulus from that direction, brokers said, money managers at investing institutions continued some selective buying of stocks in the hopes of showing good results when they make their first-quarter reports to clients at the end of this month. But otherwise, traders seemed reluctant to make any big commitments. <ORGANIZATION> TW </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> fell ~ to 27. A <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> court upheld the `` poison pill'' defense the company is employing to fight a takeover bid by <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>. Among actively traded blue chips, <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> rose -LCB- to 53; <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Carbide </ORGANIZATION> gained 1 \ to 31 ~; <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> rose \ to 30 \, and <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> was unchanged at <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Loan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mortgage </ORGANIZATION> preferred shares picked up ~ to 53. A <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> bill has been introduced that calls for the conversion of the shares to common stock and the