<HEAD>MAI Basic Four Launches Proxy Fight For Prime Computer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Intensifying the battle to take over <ORGANIZATION> Prime </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Computer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> MAI </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Basic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Four </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> said Friday it will wage a proxy fight for control of Prime's board of directors at the May 12 annual meeting. MAI Basic announced a slate of nominees for the election, which will fill all seven seats on the board by a majority vote of the stockholders represented at the meeting. Prime spokesman <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Gavaghan </PERSON> said the announcement was `` not unanticipated'' and that Prime will urge shareholders to retain the current board. MAI Basic, a computer firm based in <LOCATION> Tustin </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, launched a $ 20-per-share hostile bid for Prime in mid-November. The offer is valued at $ 970 million. In a prepared statement, <ORGANIZATION> MAI </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Basic </ORGANIZATION> said its slate of directors would be committed to selling Prime, a manufacturer of minicomputers and computer-aided design and manufacturing systems. Prime, which has headquarters in <LOCATION> Natick </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mass. </LOCATION>, issued a response saying <ORGANIZATION> MAI </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Basic </ORGANIZATION>'s bid `` continues to be highly conditional, unfinanced and extremely leveraged'' and that `` the price does not reflect the intrinsic value of Prime.'' MAI Basic's takeover offer has been enjoined since Dec. 9, when a <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> judge in <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION> ruled that MAI Basic had not disclosed sufficient information about its financing arrangements with <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Burnham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lambert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATI