 in defense contracts in fiscal 1988, with $ 3.54 billion, while <ORGANIZATION> Boeing </ORGANIZATION> ranked 10th with $ 3 billion, the <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> said this week. <ORGANIZATION> Lockheed </ORGANIZATION>'s stock also jumped late last year when <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> investor <PERSON> Harold </PERSON> <PERSON> Simmons </PERSON>, through his majority-owned <ORGANIZATION> Valhi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, sought clearance from the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> to buy up to 15 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Lockheed </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Valhi </ORGANIZATION> so far has acquired less than 1 percent of the stock.
