<FIRST>r f AM-Globex-MATIF     03-03 0295</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Globex-MATIF,0306</SECOND>
<HEAD>Merc Signs French Futures Exchange to Globex</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The French futures exchange <PERSON> Marche </PERSON> a <ORGANIZATION> Terme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> de </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> France </ORGANIZATION> has agreed to join <ORGANIZATION> Globex </ORGANIZATION>, an off-hours electronic trading system being developed by the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Reuters </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION>, officials said Thursday. The French exchange, which is known by its acronym <ORGANIZATION> MATIF </ORGANIZATION>, is the third outside exchange to announce its intention to join <ORGANIZATION> Globex </ORGANIZATION> and offer products for trading on the system. The <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, which trades primarily oil and platinum futures, and the <ORGANIZATION> Sydney </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Futures </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Australia </ORGANIZATION> previously announced plans to join <ORGANIZATION> Globex </ORGANIZATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> MATIF </ORGANIZATION> is <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>'s highest-volume futures exchange and the first in the European time zones to join <ORGANIZATION> Globex </ORGANIZATION>. It lists a variety of financial and commodity futures including a French government bond futures contract and a stock-index futures contract based on 40 stocks traded on the <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION> Bourse stock exchange. <PERSON> Leo </PERSON> <PERSON> Melamed </PERSON>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Merc </ORGANIZATION>'s executive committee, said the addition of the French exchange to <ORGANIZATION> Globex </ORGANIZATION> would give the system a partner in each of the world's three major time zones, making <ORGANIZATION> Globex </ORGANIZATION> `` the worldwide transaction system it set out to become.'' The automated system, which is expected to become operational this fall, will use a computer to match buy and sell orders during the hours that the member exchanges' trading floors are closed. The <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Merc </ORGANIZATION>, the world's second-largest futures exchange, and London-based <ORGANIZATION> Reuters </ORGANIZATION> announced plans to create the system in 1987. Futures are contracts to buy or sell a commodity or financial instrument at an agreed-upon price at a specified future date. The <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION>, the world's largest futures exchange, announced last month that it was developing its own automated off-hours trading system to compete with <ORGANIZATION> Globex </ORGANIZATION>.
